A total of 62% of respondents said they were “very satisfied” and “satisfied” with the overall quality of the relationship.
"However, 18% show themselves to be 'slightly unsatisfied' and 'very unsatisfied' in the relationship, and another 18% declare themselves 'right'," the study said in a statement.
The situation is slightly different when the responses of men and women are analyzed separately.
Thus, 28% of men are very satisfied, 39% satisfied, 17% suitable, 6% very unsatisfied and 8% slightly unsatisfied.
In terms of women, 33% said they were satisfied, 24% very satisfied, 8% very dissatisfied, 14% slightly dissatisfied and 19% chose the right category.
When we look at the degree of satisfaction (positive), we will notice that men are more satisfied.
As for the neutral state (accordingly), we see a difference of two percent.
“The same goes for the very unsatisfied situation, the biggest difference being the slightly unsatisfied response where we see a difference of 6 percent,” the statement said.
The study also showed that a quarter of Romanians (26%) spend an hour or even less time together, 18% spend between five and eight hours together, and 45% spend between two and four hours.
“Romans need a little more adventure in their lives (24%), followed by affection (21%), money (21%), security (20%), new (19%), sex (19%), respect (18%), trust 17%, pleasure 17%, connection 17%, knowledge 16%, protection 14%, importance 14%, learning 12%, freedom 11%, self-knowledge 10%.”
The study was done by Extreme Training between June 1st and September 1st on 1,369 people, with a calculated margin of error of 2.6%.
