Due to economic and demographic reasons, the prosperity they have enjoyed over the past decades can no longer continue the same in the years to come.
By Saturday, very few people knew who Jeremy Corbyn was.
Even today, after he became the new leader of the UK Labour Party, many wonder how much the choice of a politician who, after all, is not in a decision-making position can affect us.
Jeremy Corbyn is the most radical leftist leader of the post-war Labour Party.
Declared Marxist, anti-monarchist (he once asked Tony Blair, then prime minister, to remove the royal family from Buckingam Palace), a fierce anti-American and a sympathizer of Vladimir Putin (he was also regularly invited to comment on political events by the EU's "Russia Today" TV channel and the U.K. wants to re-arme the U.K. and the U.S. to re-terrorist movements)
