Following the model of all populist demagogues, Corbyn has, of course, miraculous anti-austerity solutions.
Things like what Tsipras said and promised in Greece until he came to grips with the real world and economic ties.
The economic program of the new Labour leader includes, among other things, massive renationalizations and the printing of money as a solution to finance development projects and to cover very generous social benefits.
